@startuml UC65_Apply_To_Public_Request_Sequence_Diagram

skinparam monochrome true
skinparam defaultFontColor Black
skinparam shadowing false

skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor Black
    LifeLineBorderColor Black
    LifeLineBackgroundColor White
    ParticipantBorderColor Black
    ParticipantBackgroundColor #DDDDDD
    ParticipantFontColor Black
    ActorBorderColor Black
    ActorBackgroundColor White
    ActorFontColor Black
    GroupHeaderFontColor Black
    GroupHeaderBackgroundColor White
    GroupBodyBackgroundColor White
    GroupBorderColor Black
}


title UC-65 Apply To Public Request Sequence Diagram

actor user
boundary "Marketplace Page" as Page
boundary "ProposalModal" as ProposalModal
participant "projectRequestsApi" as RequestsAPI
participant "apiClient" as ApiClient
participant "ProjectRequestsController" as Controller
participant "JwtAuthGuard" as JWTGuard
participant "RolesGuard" as RolesGuard
participant "ProjectRequestsService" as Service
participant "QuotaService" as QuotaService
database "Database" as DB

user -> Page : 1. Open a public request from the marketplace
activate user
activate Page
Page -> Page : 2. Check whether the current viewer has direct apply permission
note over Page
In the current codebase, direct self-apply is exposed for broker users.
Freelancer users stay in preview-only mode and continue through invitations.
end note
user -> Page : 3. Click "Apply" when the action is available
Page -> ProposalModal : 4. Open the proposal dialog
activate ProposalModal
user -> ProposalModal : 5. Enter a cover letter and submit the application
ProposalModal -> RequestsAPI : 6. Call applyToRequest(requestId, coverLetter)
activate RequestsAPI
RequestsAPI -> ApiClient : 7. Forward HTTP request
activate ApiClient
ApiClient -> Controller : 8. Send POST "/project-requests/{id}/apply"
activate Controller
Controller -> JWTGuard : 9. Confirm the user is signed in
activate JWTGuard
JWTGuard --> Controller : 10. Return authenticated user identity
deactivate JWTGuard
Controller -> RolesGuard : 11. Confirm the caller has direct apply permission
activate RolesGuard
RolesGuard --> Controller : 12. Role check passed
deactivate RolesGuard
Controller -> Service : 13. Create an application for the public request
activate Service
Service -> QuotaService : 14. Check apply-to-request quota and usage
activate QuotaService
QuotaService --> Service : 15. Return quota result
deactivate QuotaService
Service -> DB : 16. Load request, assignment state, and existing proposal state
activate DB
DB --> Service : 17. Return request and proposal context
deactivate DB
Service -> DB : 18. Save a new pending application
activate DB
DB --> Service : 19. Persist application record
deactivate DB
Service --> Controller : 20. Return created application
deactivate Service
Controller --> ApiClient : 21. Return server response
deactivate Controller
ApiClient --> RequestsAPI : 22. Return application success payload
deactivate ApiClient
RequestsAPI --> ProposalModal : 23. Return submitted application
deactivate RequestsAPI
ProposalModal --> Page : 24. Close the dialog and refresh the marketplace view
deactivate ProposalModal
Page --> user : 25. Show the submitted state, or keep preview-only access when direct apply is unavailable
deactivate Page
deactivate user

@enduml
